						               													<description>A quick game of intrigue and mystery that challenges your power of observation. You are the detective in a hotel that will accompany people who take the elevator. But be careful because it is very easy to lose sight of them, as they seem to disappear before your eyes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This is a game that takes place in an old European hotel. People move from floor to floor in a fascinating elevator that contains open compartments, moving in an endless chain. They enter one of the compartments while moving up and down, and then get off on another floor. Your job as a hotel detective is to follow the trail of all the mysterious characters using the elevator. Both the compartments and the characters are in constant motion, so you must use memory and logic to locate them all.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Object of the game: the 9 cards are placed face down on the table in two rows, in order to represent the elevator. A different character is shown in each compartment, they are in constant movement.&amp;#10;Players will try to be the first to guess the position of all the characters on the moving elevator cards, matching them (pair up) with the character cards in their hands.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
